th, astray, rice, road","heisig_story":"Words . . . astray.","heisig_lessonNo":"26","Keyword_KKLC":"RIDDLE, enigma","Keyword_KKLC_ru":"загадка, загадка","Keyword_KANJIDIC":"riddle, puzzle, enigma, hint, tip","Keyword_KANJIDIC_ru":"загадка, головоломка, загадка, намек, подсказка","strokeDiagram":"<img src=\"E8AC8E.png\" />","strokeCount":"16","koohiiStory1":"Words meant to lead you astray are those of a riddle.","koohiiStory2":"I led Socrates astray with my riddle. He quit philosophizing and thought only about the riddle.","jouYou":"JH","onYomi":"メイ、ベイ","kunYomi":"なぞ","jp_example_words":"謎(なぞ): riddle, puzzle, enigma","jp_readingExamples":"謎 (なぞ)","jp_sound":"[sound:oddcast-1340790d-49c3d3b6-e393ce6d-18290e68-c811f538.mp3]","WaniKani_Kanji_Meaning":"Riddle","WaniKani_Radicals":"言, 米","WaniKani_Radical_Icons":"<i class=\"radical-water-slide\"></i>","WaniKani_Radical_Names":"say, rice","WaniKani_Radical_Icons_Names":"scooter","WaniKani_Meaning_Mnemonic":"I <span class=\"radical-highlight\" title=\"Radical\" rel=\"tooltip\">say</span>, which weighs more: a kilogram of <span class=\"radical-highlight\" title=\"Radical\" rel=\"tooltip\">scooter</span>s or a kilogram of <span class=\"radical-highlight\" title=\"Radical\" rel=\"tooltip\">rice</span>? This is a <span class=\"kanji-highlight\" title=\"Kanji\" rel=\"tooltip\">riddle</span>!","WaniKani_Meaning_Info":"Think carefully and see if you can come up with the answer to my riddle before you read on.","WaniKani_Reading_Mnemonic":"Did you figure out the answer to this <span class=\"kanji-highlight\" title=\"Kanji\" rel=\"tooltip\">riddle</span>? Say your answer aloud to the screen right now.... <span class=\"reading-highlight\" title=\"Reading\" rel=\"tooltip\">not so</span> (<span lang=\"ja\">なぞ</span>)! You're wrong.","WaniKani_Reading_Info":"Did you say the answer to the riddle is that they're both a kilogram? Not so! A scooter is heavier than some rice! And don't you email me saying that's not so! It's my riddle, I can make the answer whatever I want. That's the law of riddles!","Ru_YarxiRusNick":"загадка","Ru_Meaning":"riddle, puzzle, enigma, hint, tip","Ru_Radicals":"込 (внутрь), 米 (рис), 言 (слово)","Ru_trainchinese":"<span class=\"trainchinese-pinyin\">mí</span>: (<span class=\"trainchinese-type\">сущ</span>) <span class=\"trainchinese-transl\">загадка, тайна</span>","Kanshudo_mnemonic":"the perplexing (<a href='/kanji/%E8%BF%B7'>迷</a>) words (<a href='/kanji/%E8%A8%80'>言</a>) are a riddle","chinese_mnemonics_deck__meaning":"riddle","chinese_mnemonics_deck__hanzi":"谜","chinese_mnemonics_deck__story":"A bunch of words that makes you feel really lost is a riddle.","chinese_mnemonics_deck__diagram":"<img src='lf_35868.gif'/>","chinese_mnemonics_deck__kind":"traditional","chinese_mnemonics_deck__equiv":"谜","humanum_full_description_en":"From &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%A8%80\">words</a> &quot; to &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%BF%B7\">fans</a> &quot;, &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%BF%B7\">fans</a> &quot; also sound. The original meaning is cryptic and riddle. &quot;Jade articles. Yan Bu: &quot;Mystery, hidden words.&quot; &quot;Shu Wen Xin Attached&quot;: &quot;Riddles, hidden words. From words, fans, fans also sound.&quot; Such as &quot;Wen Xin Diao Long. Humor&quot;: &quot;Since the Wei Dynasty has come, it is quite a haiyu, but the gentleman mocks and hides and turns into a riddle. The riddle also turns into a coma.&quot; Feng Menglong of the Ming Dynasty &quot;Jing Shi Tong Yan. &quot;Jin Lingshi, Maid&#39;s Maid Rewarding Xiu Tong&quot;: &quot;Brother, you must be what you see. Don&#39;t try to guess again!&quot;<br><br> &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%AC%8E\">Mystery</a> &quot; is also a metaphor for things that have not been understood or are difficult to understand. For example, Lao She&#39;s &quot;Four Generations Under One Roof&quot;: &quot;In terms of thought, speech, and some actions, Rui Xuan is simply an unsolvable mystery of her.&quot;","humanum_short_description_en":"From &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%A8%80\">words</a> &quot; to &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%BF%B7\">fans</a> &quot;, &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%BF%B7\">fans</a> &quot; also sound. The original meaning is cryptic and riddle.","humanum_full_description":"從「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%A8%80\">言</a>」從「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%BF%B7\">迷</a>」，「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%BF%B7\">迷</a>」亦聲。本義是隱語、謎語。《玉篇．言部》：「謎，隱言也。」《說文新附》：「謎，隱語也。从言、迷，迷亦聲。」如《文心雕龍．諧讔》：「自魏代已來，頗非俳優，而君子嘲隱，化為謎語。謎也者，迴互其辭，使昏迷也。」明代馮夢龍《警世通言．金令史美婢酬秀童》：「好兄弟，你須是眼見的實，莫又做猜謎的話！」<br> <br> 　　「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%AC%8E\">謎</a>」也比喻還沒有弄明白或難以理解的事物。如老舍《四世同堂》：「在思想上、言論上和一部分行動上，瑞宣簡直是她的一個永不可解的謎。」","humanum_short_description":"從「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%A8%80\">言</a>」從「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%BF%B7\">迷</a>」，「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%BF%B7\">迷</a>」亦聲。本義是隱語、謎語。","humanum_img_url":"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/kangxiArchaic.php?hash=183a0396ba4c33ded37cdf442c3a618b","_purpleculture_dictionary_orig_full":"<div class=\"d-flex\"><div style=\"line-height:1.6\"><div id=\"sen0\"><ruby class=\"mainsc\">謎</ruby> <span class=\"tc\">(Simplified: 谜)</span><label class=\"hskbadge col-form-label ml-2\">HSK 6</label><div class=\"btn-group px-2\"></div></div><div class=\"clearBoth\"></div><div class=\"c